**Case 1:** $R \circ T$ (translate first, then reflect)
$$
 P(1, 2) &\xrightarrow{T} (5, 2) \xrightarrow{R} (-5, 2)
$$

**Case 2:** $T \circ R$ (reflect first, then translate)
$$
 P(1, 2) &\xrightarrow{R} (-1, 2) \xrightarrow{T} (3, 2)
$$

The results are different! $R \circ T$ gives $(-5, 2)$ while 
$T \circ R$ gives $(3, 2)$.

