tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 % Grid
 (-6,-1) grid (6,4);
 (-6,0) – (6.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-1) – (0,4.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Original point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (1,2) circle (4pt);
 at (1,2.3) {$P(1,2)$};

 % R∘T path
 ll[AtlasWarm] (5,2) circle (3pt);
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-5,2) circle (4pt);
 at (-5,2.3) {$(-5,2)$};
 (1,2) – (4.7,2);
 (5,2) – (-4.7,2);
 at (2.5,3) {$R \circ T$};

 % T∘R path
 ll[AtlasSage] (-1,2) circle (3pt);
 ll[AtlasSage] (3,2) circle (4pt);
 at (3,1.6) {$(3,2)$};
tikzpicture
center

**Step 1:** Translate by $\langle 5, 0 \rangle$:
\[
 P(2, 3) \to (7, 3)
\]

**Step 2:** Reflect over the $x$-axis:
\[
 (7, 3) \to (7, -3)
\]

The image under the glide reflection is $(7, -3)$.

